The paper focuses on using computer vision techniques, specifically Convolutional Neural Networks (CNN) and Long Short Term Memory (LSTM), for crowd counting in still images. This falls under the computer vision subfield of computer science, which is categorized under cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). Additionally, the use of deep learning models such as CNN and LSTM suggests that the paper may also fall under the subcategories of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also involves the use of datasets and experiments, which may fall under cs.MM (Multimedia) and cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
